<subSubSection id="C36E6574067DFFED82E5FAE8FDC601D8" pageId="0" pageNumber="107" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BCB36FF067DFFED82E5FAE8FDC601D8" blockId="0.[136,1452,1297,1790]" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">
<emphasis id="B900EAED067DFFED82E5FAE8FEB302F8" bold="true" box="[189,262,1478,1502]" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">Notes:</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C744D7C067DFFED8357FAE8FE0A02F8" authorityName="Merrill K" authorityYear="1922" box="[271,447,1478,1502]" class="Liliopsida" family="Smilacaceae" genus="Smilax" kingdom="Plantae" order="Liliales" pageId="0" pageNumber="107" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="gigantea">
<emphasis id="B900EAED067DFFED8357FAE8FE0A02F8" box="[271,447,1478,1502]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">Smilax gigantea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was described by Elmer Drew Merrill in 1922 based on the collections made from British North Borneo near Sandakan by 
<collectorName id="26815329067DFFED83BFFAC4FDE30127" box="[487,598,1514,1537]" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">
M. 
<location id="8EAB6024067DFFED8054FAC4FDE30127" LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:03DD87E9067DFFED82D0FA3CFDC601D8:8EAB6024067DFFED8054FAC4FDE30127" box="[524,598,1514,1537]" country="United States of America" name="Ramos in November" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">Ramos</location>
</collectorName>
in November, 1920. While searching for the type specimen of 
<emphasis id="B900EAED067DFFED86A0FAC4FA1E0124" box="[1272,1451,1514,1538]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">
<taxonomicName id="4C744D7C067DFFED86A0FAC4FA120124" authorityName="Merrill K" authorityYear="1922" box="[1272,1447,1514,1538]" class="Liliopsida" family="Smilacaceae" genus="Smilax" kingdom="Plantae" order="Liliales" pageId="0" pageNumber="107" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="gigantea">Smilax gigantea</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
we found that Ramosâ collections were housed at various herbaria 
<emphasis id="B900EAED067DFFED8106F921FC360100" box="[862,899,1551,1574]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">viz.</emphasis>
, A, BO, BR, C, CAL, CM, DPU, E, G, GH, K, L, MANCH, MO, NSW, NY, P, PNH, SAN, U, 
<collectingCountry id="F363766F067DFFED803FF91CFD3C016C" box="[615,649,1586,1610]" name="United States of America" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">US</collectingCountry>
and WRSL and after a thorough search, we could locate five duplicates for this collection, one each at P (P00686981), K (K000292107), 
<collectingCountry id="F363766F067DFFED8170F978FCFF0148" box="[808,842,1622,1646]" name="United States of America" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">US</collectingCountry>
(00092004), A (00030119) and L (L1453511). All these specimens have 
<collectorName id="26815329067DFFED836EF954FE1E01B4" box="[310,427,1658,1682]" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">M. Ramosâ</collectorName>
annotation as â 
<taxonomicName id="4C744D7C067DFFED8008F954FC8B01B7" authority="Merr." authorityName="Merr." authorityYear="2022" box="[592,830,1658,1682]" class="Liliopsida" family="Smilacaceae" genus="Smilax" kingdom="Plantae" order="Liliales" pageId="0" pageNumber="107" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="gigantea" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis id="B900EAED067DFFED8008F954FD4901B4" box="[592,764,1658,1682]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">Smilax gigantea</emphasis>
Merr.
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A2335796067DFFED811BF954FCC801B7" box="[835,893,1658,1681]" pageId="0" pageNumber="107" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, 1850, Sandakan and vicinity, Sept-Dec, 1920, Flora of British North Borneoâ. Out of these, specimen K000292107 is designated as a 
<typeStatus id="54CF885D067DFFED8656F9B0FBC60190" box="[1038,1139,1694,1718]" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">lectotype</typeStatus>
, following articles 7.11, 9.3, and 9.12 of the ICN (
<bibRefCitation id="EFE54B0E067DFFED8337F9ECFDF601FC" author="Turland, N. J. &amp; Wiersema, J. H. &amp; Barrie, F. R. &amp; Greuter, W. &amp; Hawksworth, D. L. &amp; Herendeen, P. S. &amp; Knapp, S. &amp; Kusber, W. - H. &amp; Li, D. - Z. &amp; Marhold, K. &amp; May, T. W. &amp; McNeill, J. &amp; Monro, A. M. &amp; Prado, J. &amp; Price, M. J. &amp; Smith, G. F." box="[367,579,1730,1754]" pageId="0" pageNumber="107" refId="ref2863" refString="Turland, N. J., Wiersema, J. H., Barrie, F. R., Greuter, W., Hawksworth, D. L., Herendeen, P. S., Knapp, S., Kusber, W. - H., Li, D. - Z., Marhold, K., May, T. W., McNeill, J., Monro, A. M., Prado, J., Price, M. J. &amp; Smith, G. F. (Eds.) (2018) International Code of Nomenclature for algae, fungi, and plants (Shenzhen Code) adopted by the Nineteenth International Botanical Congress Shenzhen, China, July 2017. Regnum Vegetabile 159. Glashutten: Koeltz Botanical Books, 254 pp. https: // doi. org / 10.12705 / Code. 2018" type="book" year="2018">
Turland 
<emphasis id="B900EAED067DFFED8393F9EDFE4E01FC" box="[459,507,1730,1754]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">et al</emphasis>
. 2018
</bibRefCitation>
). This specimen matches perfectly with the protologue description and bears the branches and inflorescence in good condition.
</paragraph>
